      "message": "[Critical] Line 2809: For one-to-one conversations, `isPeerAuthorized()` now delegates to `Conversation::isPeerAuthorized()`, which checks conversation membership/ban files instead of preserving the previous one-to-one trust-store-only authorization behavior used by `isBanned()`. This can reject valid one-to-one peers if the local conversation repository is not fully initialized or membership state differs from the trust store. Handle `ConversationMode::ONE_TO_ONE` explicitly after the trust-store checks, e.g. return true when neither member nor device certificate is banned, or otherwise apply the existing one-to-one authorization semantics.",
