      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 2423: `onConversationNeedSwarmSocket()` only checks `isDeviceBanned(convId, deviceId)`. The rest of the patch hardens git/conversation/swarm incoming paths with `isPeerAuthorized()` to reject banned members, non-members, and device/member mismatches, but this outgoing swarm socket path still allows connecting to a device whose owner is no longer authorized as long as the device itself is not banned. Resolve the device owner and use the same peer authorization check before connecting, or ensure the callback receives enough peer identity to validate both the member URI and device ID.",
